From 5a6dc73d2568ceb1906bc48fad84b8f2b1b6246b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nishant Sharma <nishant.sharma@arm.com>
Date: Mon, 12 Feb 2024 13:25:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 36/78] Sgi: Move StMM communication carveout out of secure
 region.

The non secure buffer carveout overlaps with the secure DRAM carvout.
TZC does not allow overlapping carveout and when enabled cause abort to
any access made to that region. Previous version of TZC had a bug which
did not detect this.

Signed-off-by: Nishant Sharma <nishant.sharma@arm.com>
Change-Id: Ie39ed8d819f85b1a63f8e03bfbb80d7a7fd66cf8
---
 Platform/ARM/SgiPkg/AcpiTables/RdN2Cfg1/Einj.aslc | 12 ++++++------
 Platform/ARM/SgiPkg/SgiPlatform.dsc.inc           |  6 +++---
 Platform/ARM/SgiPkg/SgiPlatformMm.dsc.inc         |  4 ++--
 3 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Platform/ARM/SgiPkg/AcpiTables/RdN2Cfg1/Einj.aslc b/Platform/ARM/SgiPkg/AcpiTables/RdN2Cfg1/Einj.aslc
